reviews.text: The food itself is okay and is reasonably priced. But the service of one particular waitress is TERRIBLE. First she never smiled and at the end of every conversation she would put a long face🤯. Ok maybe she’s tired or maybe she’s having mood swing. Second she put the dishes randomly or just at the edge of the table as long as it’s convenient for her to dispose of the dishes. Sometimes she even put it on the unused tissue paper🤯 Third she served the dish with an attitude - just put the dish on the table as hard as she could. For one moment the egg cube was too soft and at the moment she put the plate of the table one of the egg cubes fell on the table🤯. Fourth she urged us to leave the cafe when it’s time for them to close the shop BY TAPPING HER FINGERS ON HER WATCH without saying anything🤯🤯🤯 Really impressive service!
Nice food and comfortable, a little bit over priced

5 star for food, 1 star for the service of that particular staff.
Shall start off with the very poor service by this particular staff which spoilt our impression of the place. Our friend booked a table for 5pax (surprise but welcome it). First impressions of the place was cool and chic, not expecting to find such a cafe in this area. But the moment we sat down, only one set of menu was given to us (note it is A5 paper size).
1. We asked the staff (shall refer her as the villain) for another set of menu, she got one and threw it on the table, which got us startled.
2. We wanted to place our order, villain gave us eye contact & pause at our table, seems that she wants to get our order. Out of the sudden, that was a fake move and she went to the other table, leaving us in a limbo. Fortunately we managed to get the attention of the other staff and placed our order. 
3. When serving one of our dishes, again villain threw it on the table which resulted in the food tumbling onto the table right infront of us. Of course she apologise for it and got the kitchen to replace it.
4. When it was time for last order, she came around table to table. When we asked villain for the menu, she just gave us an 😲 looks as though we are asking an outrageous request. 
5. We stayed on beyond their closing hour to chit-chatting (we are grateful about that) till they needed us to go. But the manner villain decided to announce was shockingly. Villain just went up to us and tapping furiously on her invisible watch to get us to go. 🤯

Beside the lousy service, food wise was spot on and dessert was simply lovely (special mentioned to the mini waffles). Highly recommend for one to come by the food.

They have alcoholic drinks/cocktails too. Hope that villain is not the boss relative or she is a big turn off for customers.
Owner is too handsome!

reviews.text: 食物尚算好味，只是飯質有點硬，不過服務質素要改善；話説某星期六下午光顧，顧客不算很多，但安排座位後，遲遲沒有侍應遞上餐牌，落單想飲杯咖啡，但侍應生回覆只有齋啡……ok, 改了檸茶後，不久有其他顧客光顧及想落單一杯咖啡(只相隔十分鐘)，同一女侍應就回覆“咖啡及奶會分開上”！？    WTF！！！！
飯質有點硬，蛋做形得但欠旦未，咖哩喺日系味道還可以，炸雞都算唔錯，總括嚟講，有心煮食但原材料質素一般。

有種去了小旅行的感覺
是日式咖哩配唐揚雞的蛋包飯🍛
餐飲點了泡沫咖啡☕️

蛋包飯同生姜燒係我地既恆常選擇
鷄扒脆皮無雪味，咖哩汁有蔬菜蓉既質感同甜味，撈飯食吾錯，個蛋皮捲得好靚。今日個生姜燒硬左d, 味道正常。反而跟餐是日特飲偶有驚喜。
如果可以經常轉換餐牌多D選擇更佳。
